Interactive Map of New Orleans¶

With crime data from March 17 to March 21, 2023¶

Using open street map, incident cluster map, and heatmap¶

In [22]:
import math

import folium
from folium import (
    Choropleth,
    Circle,
    Marker,
)
from folium.plugins import (
    HeatMap,
    MarkerCluster,
)
import pandas as pd

pd.set_option("display.max_rows", 8)

Remove empty rows¶

In [7]:
crime_data = crime_data[
    crime_data["Zip"] != "None"]

Convert location from points to longitude and latitude¶

In [25]:
long_lat = crime_data["Location"].map(lambda x: x.lstrip("POINT (").rstrip(")")).str.split(" ", expand=True)
In [26]:
crime_data["Long"] = long_lat.loc[:, 0]
crime_data["Lat"] = long_lat.loc[:, 1]

Change the TimeCreate to a datetime¶

In [27]:
crime_data["TimeCreate"] = pd.to_datetime(
    crime_data["TimeCreate"],
    format="%m/%d/%Y %I:%M:%S %p")

Filter the dataframe down to last visit timeframe¶

In [28]:
filter_crime_data = crime_data.loc[
    (crime_data["TimeCreate"] >= "2023-03-17")
    & (crime_data["TimeCreate"] < "2023-03-21")]

Add crime locations to cluster map¶

In [16]:
for idx, row in crime_map_df.iterrows():
#     iframe = folium.IFrame(f"Type: {row['InitialTypeText']}" + "<br>" + f"Date: {row['TimeCreate']}", height=50)
#     info_popup = folium.Popup(iframe, min_width=300, max_width=300)
    crime_mc.add_child(Marker(
        location=[row["Lat"], row["Long"]],
#         popup=info_popup))
        popup=f"""{row['InitialTypeText']} \n {row['TimeCreate']}"""))
